con_ges_tion
 /kənˋdʒɛstʃən/


congestion = 擁擠 / 堵塞 / 堵車 / 鼻塞

1. 當作主詞 (Subject)
用來描述某種「擁擠現象」帶來的影響。
Traffic congestion is a major problem in Taipei. (交通擁擠是台北的一個大問題。)
Nasal congestion makes it hard to sleep. (鼻塞讓人很難入睡。)

2. 當作受詞 (Object)
放在動詞（如 lead to, cause, relieve）或介係詞之後。
動詞後： The accident caused severe traffic congestion. (這場事故造成了嚴重的交通堵塞。)
動詞後： This medicine helps relieve nasal congestion. (這款藥有助於緩解鼻塞。)
介係詞後： We are looking for a solution to traffic congestion. (我們正在尋找解決交通擁擠的方法。)



traffic congestion 
traffic congestion is frustrating.
road congestion
road congestion is common in Taipei.
nasal congestion
nasal congestion is annoying.



 1️⃣ 交通堵塞
There is heavy traffic congestion in the city.
I was late because of road congestion.

2️⃣ 鼻子堵塞
I have nasal congestion from a cold.
The medicine helps reduce congestion.

I’m stuck in traffic congestion.
My nose is blocked because of congestion.


⚠️ 小提醒
congestion = 名詞
congested = 形容詞（形容地方很塞）
The roads are congested today.
